commit_list.message:
gomock.WithContext: controller with a context which is cancelled on Fatals.

testing.T.FailNow (and Fatal, ...) work only when called from the same
goroutine as the test. This makes using gomock with e.g. RPC server
mocks quite a challenge as the tests are likely to deadlock instead of
failing properly.

This adds a new constructor returning an additional context, which is
cancelled on any fatal failure in mock.

commit_list.message:
HTTP Header customization for authenticators.

BasicAuth and DigestAuth now use Headers struct which contains header
names checked and sent back when doing authentication as well as
"Unauthorized" error code and response used.

Code defaults to NormalHeaders which is backwards-compatible with old
implementation. Also there are ProxyHeaders which allow to use same
authenticators for the HTTP Proxy server request authentication.

x/tools/tour: support for golang.org/x/tools/imports.

This adds a new toggle, which, when enabled, uses goimports instead of
gofmt to format and auto-add imports on "format" requests.

Fixes #17886.

Check for redundant if err != nil constructs. (#319)

* Check for redundant if err != nil constructs.

Detect and complain about constructs like:

if err := foo(); err != nil {
  return err
}
return nil

(Issue https://github.com/golang/lint/issues/312)

* Rewrite lintIfError without using matchers.

Also don't emit lint errors if there are any comments explaining the
construct (between if and return statements).
